To get this code working on a new machine:

1. Install the Enthought Python Distribution
2. Install Install MOSEK and its python API

3. Install mpich2 (so mpirun command is recognized) and make sure it is used instead of openmpi
wget http://www.mcs.anl.gov/research/projects/mpich2/downloads/tarballs/1.4.1p1/mpich2-1.4.1p1.tar.gz
--NOTE: openmpi seems to have bugs, so switched to mpich2 (e.g. https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups=#!topic/mpi4py/UJrEavb3mXM)
On a machine without a fortran compiler like pawan's special flags are needed:

./configure --prefix=/PATH/TO/mpich2-install --disable-f77 --disable-fc CFLAGS=-fPIC CXXFLAGS=-fPIC FFLAGS=-fPIC FCFLAGS=-fPIC 2>&1 | tee c.txt
make 2>&1 | tee m.txt
make install 2>&1 | tee mi.txt

4. Install mpi4py module
5. Add the data and output directories for your machine to config.py
6. easy_install psutil


Here is a sample .profile file that properly prepares the environment for a run:

# For research purposes, use locally-installed software
LOCAL=$HOME/local
export PATH=$PATH:$LOCAL/git/bin
export PATH=$LOCAL/epd-7.3-2-rh5-x86_64/bin:$PATH
export MOSEKHOME=$LOCAL/mosek
export MOSEKLM_LICENSE_FILE=$MOSEKHOME/6/licenses
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:$MOSEKHOME/6/tools/platform/linux64x86/bin
export PATH=$PATH:$LOCAL/openmpi-1.6.1/bin
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:$LOCAL/openmpi-1.6.1/lib


